data.name: Chinese Black Pepper Beef Stir-Fry with Broccoli
data.quickTastyDescription: A quick and flavorful stir-fry featuring tender beef, crisp broccoli, and a zesty black pepper sauce.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix soy sauce, black pepper, garlic, ginger, and cornstarch to create a marinade.
Add the sliced beef to the marinade and let it sit for about 5-10 minutes.
Heat cooking oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.
Add the marinated beef to the skillet and stir-fry for about 3-4 minutes until browned.
Add the broccoli and water to the skillet, cover, and steam for 2-3 minutes until the broccoli is bright green and tender-crisp.
Remove the lid and stir everything together, cooking for another minute until the sauce thickens slightly.
Serve hot over cooked rice or noodles.
data.detailedName: Easy Chinese Black Pepper Beef Stir-Fry with Broccoli
